                               QCK SHELL
                               =========
			  by Aiden Whitehead
			  ------------------
			  
This is Qck Shell, a simple (terrible) toy shell I have been making in
order to teach myself UNIX syscalls, to improve my knowledge of the C
programming language, and to figure out how to use git.

Qck Shell is intended to eventually implement most of the functionality
of the Bourne shell (as if the world needs yet another clone of the
Bourne shell), but I have not strayed away from significantly
simplifying and changing what Bourne shell does when I am unable to
think of a good way to implement what the Bourne shell does.  For
example, one of the most significant changes is that, unlike the true
Bourne shell which doesn't care how you type your pipes/redirects/etc.
(i.e., "foo|bar", "foo |bar", etc.), Qck Shell (at least in its current
state) requires that all tokens be separated by whitespace (i.e., only
"foo | bar", nothing else).

If anyone happens to look at this repo and sees anything that I did
incorrectly/poorly, I will graciously accept any criticism whatsoever.
I know for a fact that much of what I have done has not been done in
the best (or even a correct) manner, so I welcome the chance to be
corrected on the errors I made.

Thank you for reading!